Based on practical examples, the subject gives an overview of how the clinical pharmacist can contribute to the optimization of the treatment regimens of patients with infectious diseases and in pain management. As homework, students solve clinical cases about optimizing a patient's treatment regimen. In the webinar, there will be a discussion based on clinical cases.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the subject is to provide an overview of the most common infectious diseases and to discuss the peculiarities of drug administration and the role of the clinical pharmacist in optimizing treatment regimens for patients with infections.The purpose of the module is to provide an overview about use of analgetics and the role of clinical pharmacist in the pain management team.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the subject: * knows the principles of practicing clinical pharmacy in the treatment of pain and infections * has the necessary knowledge of the principles of antimicrobial and antiviral treatment for a clinical pharmacist * knows analgetics and  the principles of their use and selection * has knowledge of how to advise doctors, nurses and patients regarding pain treatment and pharmacological treatment for infectious diseases  * knows the principles of antimicrobial resistance management and can apply them * identifies and analyzes bottlenecks in pharmacotherapy from a clinical pharmacist's point of view.
